comments: Ivey (DET) makes lower body contact with Brown (LAC) as he defends the shot near the rim.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Kennard's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs when the two players engage and disengage as the pick is set.
Batum (LAC) and Bogdanovic (DET) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Bogdanovic (DET) establishes himself in Kennard's (LAC) path and does not deliver contact.
Brown (LAC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Hayes (DET).
Hayes (DET) and Coffey (LAC) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs in the backcourt.
Hayes (DET) avoids making contact with the ball while he is out of bounds.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Mann's (LAC) path and does not deliver contact.
Mann (LAC) legally contests Hayes' (DET) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Duren (DET) brings his left forearm towards Brown (LAC) and marginal contact occurs as Duren releases for the ball.
Bogdanovic (DET) establishes himself in Coffey's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact to his upper body.
Batum (LAC) is moving alongside Burks' (DET) path and marginal contact occurs as Burks cuts back towards the rim.
As he returns to the floor, Mann's (LAC) forearm brushes Burks' (DET) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Burks falls to the floor on his own.
Hayes (DET) swipes his arm down and initiates contact with Kennard (LAC) that affects his SQBR.
Brown (LAC) places his hand momentarily on Duren's (DET) side and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Duren (DET) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Duren (DET) is firming up over his left leg and he absorbs the contact from Kennard (LAC).
Coffey (LAC) legally contests Burks' (DET) jump shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) is bracing for the contact from Ivey (DET) and marginal contact occurs as Mann releases away from the contact.
Diallo (DET) moves laterally into George's (LAC) path and delivers contact that affects his SQBR.
Mann (LAC) commits a take foul on Hayes (DET).

Stewart (DET) brushes George's (LAC) head/face after George has secured the rebound, and the marginal contact occurs after the timeout has been awarded to LAC.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Zubac (LAC) and Stewart (DET) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Mann (LAC) and Stewart (DET) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.

George (LAC) brings the ball to his hip and loses control as he attempts to gather the ball. He then legally re-gains control of the ball and does not resume his dribble after gathering the loose ball.
Stewart (DET) legally contests Mann's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
As Bogdanovic (DET) and Kennard (LAC) move towards the basket, incidental leg to leg contact occurs as they come together at the same spot.
Bogdanovic (DET) is bracing for the contact from Batum (LAC) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Kennard (LAC) legally contests Bogdanovic's (DET) jump shot attempt.
